						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">NewRisingSun wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">This is very important, and implies that the same television with the same console would produce pictures of different brightness between a baseband composite connection and an RF-modulated connection.</div> Yes, but the usual AGC is on sync depth, normalizing it to -40 IRE. There's no clearly correct thing to do if given contradictory gains needed to normalize both colorburst and sync depth.</div>

